AbilityScoreFeature.Name: Ability Score Increase
AbilityScoreFeature.Text: Your Strength score increases by 2, and your Constitution score increases by 1.

Feature.Name: Age
Feature.Text: Keldons reach adulthood in their late teens and live less than a century.

Feature.Name: Alignment
Feature.Text: Keldons tend toward chaotic alignments, and many walk a fine line between good and evil.

Feature.Name: Size
Feature.Text: Keldons are taller and heavier than the human norms of other cultures, standing almost universally above 6 feet tall and reaching heights above 7 feet. Your size is Medium.

SpeedFeature.Name: Speed
SpeedFeature.Text: Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

LanguageProficiencyFeature.Name: Languages
LanguageProficiencyFeature.Text: You can speak, read, and write Common and Keldon.

SkillProficiencyFeature.Name: Natural Athlete
SkillProficiencyFeature.Text: You have proficiency in the Athletics skill.

SaveProficiencyFeature.Name: Keldon Resilience
SaveProficiencyFeature.Text: You have proficiency in Strength saving throws.

Feature.Name: Icehaven Born
Feature.Text: You are naturally adapted to cold climates, as described in chapter 5 of the Dungeon Master’s Guide.

Race.Name: Keldon
Race.Description: The people of Keld are human, but they are like no other humans anywhere. Nearly all adults stand over six feet tall, and heights above seven feet are not uncommon. They are massively muscled and have gray skin, ranging from an ashy gray-white to a deeper bluegray. The typical Keldon’s hairline points sharply down in the middle of the forehead and at either temple, but recedes elsewhere—sometimes dramatically. Keldons are remarkably resistant to the cold of their homeland, baring skin even in near-freezing temperatures without discomfort. Keldons value self-reliance, strength, and courage above all else. Anything that is the product of their own labor is a fine thing. Anything else is treated with a healthy dose of skepticism. At best, they are a proud, pragmatic, passionate people, and their loyalty is fierce once earned. At worst, they can be reckless, hot-tempered, and violent—and no small number of Keldons still consider these qualities virtues rather than vices. Because of their many exploits as both conquerors and mercenaries, Keldons appear in the legends and histories of other peoples across the world. Sometimes these tales are exaggerated—but many that sound exaggerated are not.

Description.Name: Keldon Human Traits
Description.Text: The humans of Keld have the following traits, which replace the standard human traits presented in the Player’s Handbook.
